wlanTip: Displays WLAN lists. Click on each row to see related monitoring and client information in the corresponding display area, you can also see the details of WLAN by clicking the title.
apTip: Click on each row in AP list to see the monitoring and client information of this AP in the corresponding display area, you can also see the details of each AP by clicking the title.
clientTip: Click on each row in the clients lists, you can see the monitoring information of each client, and you can also get the details of clients by clicking the title.
monitorTip: This module displays statistics information for each AP WLAN or client.
systemTip: This is the first level menu that shows the basic system information. Click here to fold or unfold it.
clusterTip: This area displays the cluster information, you can click here to view the details.
syslogTip: This area displays the AP's syslog information and the configuration of Syslog.
systemTime: This area displays the AP's Date & Time, timezone and NTP server information and  manage  this.

RoguAPTip: Rogue AP statistical information. Click here to see the details.
accessTip: This is the first level of menu that shows information about authentication and the related rules. Click here to fold or unfold it.
authTip: Authentication information about local portal. Click here to see the details.
aclTip: ACL rules. Click here to see the details.
FilterTip: Configure user blacklists and whitelists, walled garden.
